Allow PKCE/S256 OIDC apps to omit client_secret.

Upstream: oauth2-proxy/oauth2-proxy#3168 (open since Aug 2025,
unmerged at time of factory deploy 2026). Without this, a Zitadel
"PKCE / none" OIDC app -- which Zitadel deliberately doesn't issue a
client_secret for -- can't be used with oauth2-proxy: startup
validation refuses to launch the container.

Fix is 5 lines in pkg/validation/providers.go: short-circuit the
"provider requires client_secret" check when both Type=oidc and
CodeChallengeMethod=S256 are set.

Tests for the new branch (test file change in the upstream PR)
omitted from this patch -- nixpkgs' buildGoModule for oauth2-proxy
doesn't run the test suite by default, so they'd be dead weight.

Source: https://github.com/oauth2-proxy/oauth2-proxy/pull/3168.patch

--- a/pkg/validation/providers.go
+++ b/pkg/validation/providers.go
@@ -68,6 +68,11 @@ func providerRequiresClientSecret(provider options.Provider) bool {
 		return false
 	}

+	// PKCE with S256 doesn't require client secret
+	if provider.Type == "oidc" && provider.CodeChallengeMethod == "S256" {
+		return false
+	}
+
 	if provider.Type == "login.gov" {
 		return false
 	}
